{
  "id": "tapestry-delegation-parallel-batch-detection",
  "title": "Tapestry delegates parallel-safe tasks in the same response",
  "description": "Checks that Tapestry identifies tasks with disjoint file sets as parallel-safe and delegates them in a single response, while keeping tasks with overlapping files sequential.",
  "phase": "experimental",
  "tags": ["experimental", "tapestry", "delegation-contract", "parallelism"],
  "target": {
    "kind": "builtin-agent-prompt",
    "agent": "tapestry"
  },
  "executor": {
    "kind": "model-response",
    "provider": "openrouter",
    "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-20250514",
    "input": "You are executing /start-work on a plan with 3 unchecked tasks:\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Add user service\n  **Files**: src/services/user.ts\n  **What**: Create a user service with CRUD operations\n  **Acceptance**: UserService class exported from src/services/user.ts\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Add product service\n  **Files**: src/services/product.ts\n  **What**: Create a product service with CRUD operations\n  **Acceptance**: ProductService class exported from src/services/product.ts\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Update user service with product reference\n  **Files**: src/services/user.ts\n  **What**: Add a method to user service that references products\n  **Acceptance**: UserService has a getProductsForUser method\n\nAnalyse the tasks and describe how you would delegate them. Which tasks can run in parallel and which must be sequential?"
  },
  "evaluators": [
    {
      "kind": "llm-judge",
      "expectedAnyOf": ["Task 1 and Task 2 can run concurrently", "Tasks 1 and 2 can be delegated in the same response", "delegate Task 1 and Task 2 together", "batch Task 1 and Task 2", "run Task 1 and Task 2 simultaneously", "delegate Tasks 1 and 2 together while Task 3 waits", "Task 3 must wait for Task 1", "parallel", "Task 1 and Task 2", "tasks 1 and 2", "simultaneously", "same response", "concurrently"],
      "forbiddenContains": ["Task 3 in parallel with Task 1", "all three in parallel", "all tasks simultaneously"]
    }
  ]
}
